    /* UtmzUtils */
    (function() {

        var utmzCookieValues = null;

        function _getUtmzCookieValue() {
            var val = (document.cookie.match(/^(?:.*;)?\s__utmz=([^;]+)(?:.*)?$/)||[,null])[1];
            return val;
        }

        function _getUtmzCookieValues() {
            if (utmzCookieValues !== null) {
                return utmzCookieValues;
            }
            else {
                var utmzCookieValue = _getUtmzCookieValue();
                if (utmzCookieValue !== null) {
                    var pairs = utmzCookieValue.split('.').slice(4).join('.').split('|');
                    var ga = {};
                    for (var i = 0; i < pairs.length; i++) {
                        var temp = pairs[i].split('=');
                        ga[temp[0]] = temp[1];
                    }
                    utmzCookieValues = ga;
                    return utmzCookieValues;
                }
                else {
                    utmzCookieValues = {};
                    return utmzCookieValues;
                }
            }
        }

        function getValue(name) {
            var val = _getUtmzCookieValues()[name];
            return (typeof(val) !== 'undefined' ? val : '');
        }

        window.UtmzUtils = {
            getValue: getValue,
            _getUtmzCookieValue: _getUtmzCookieValue,
            _getUtmzCookieValues: _getUtmzCookieValues
        };

    })();
</script>

Appendix

Alert types

This section contains additional information on the types of alerts in the report.

  1. Absence of Anti-CSRF Tokens

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Absence of Anti-CSRF Tokens)
    CWE ID 352
    WASC ID 9
    Reference
    1. https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross-Site_Request_Forgery_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html
    2. https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/352.html

  2. Content Security Policy (CSP) Header Not Set

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Content Security Policy (CSP) Header Not Set)
    CWE ID 693
    WASC ID 15
    Reference
    1. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/CSP/Introducing_Content_Security_Policy
    2. https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Content_Security_Policy_Cheat_Sheet.html
    3. https://www.w3.org/TR/CSP/
    4. https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-csp/
    5. https://web.dev/articles/csp
    6. https://caniuse.com/#feat=contentsecuritypolicy
    7. https://content-security-policy.com/

  3. Cross-Domain Misconfiguration

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Cross-Domain Misconfiguration)
    CWE ID 264
    WASC ID 14
    Reference
    1. https://vulncat.fortify.com/en/detail?id=desc.config.dotnet.html5_overly_permissive_cors_policy

  4. Missing Anti-clickjacking Header

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Anti-clickjacking Header)
    CWE ID 1021
    WASC ID 15
    Reference
    1. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Frame-Options

  5. Vulnerable JS Library

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Vulnerable JS Library (Powered by Retire.js))
    CWE ID 829
    Reference
    1. https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2012-6708
    2. https://github.com/jquery/jquery/issues/2432
    3. http://research.insecurelabs.org/jquery/test/
    4. https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2019-11358
    5. https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-rmxg-73gg-4p98
    6. https://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/11974
    7. https://github.com/jquery/jquery.com/issues/162
    8. https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2020-7656
    9. https://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/9521
    10. http://blog.jquery.com/2016/01/08/jquery-2-2-and-1-12-released/
    11. http://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/11290
    12. https://blog.jquery.com/2019/04/10/jquery-3-4-0-released/
    13. https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2015-9251
    14. https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-q4m3-2j7h-f7xw
    15. https://github.com/jquery/jquery/commit/753d591aea698e57d6db58c9f722cd0808619b1b
    16. https://blog.jquery.com/2020/04/10/jquery-3-5-0-released/
    17. https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2011-4969

  6. Cookie No HttpOnly Flag

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Cookie No HttpOnly Flag)
    CWE ID 1004
    WASC ID 13
    Reference
    1. https://owasp.org/www-community/HttpOnly

  7. Cookie Without Secure Flag

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Cookie Without Secure Flag)
    CWE ID 614
    WASC ID 13
    Reference
    1. https://owasp.org/www-project-web-security-testing-guide/v41/4-Web_Application_Security_Testing/06-Session_Management_Testing/02-Testing_for_Cookies_Attributes.html

  8. Cookie with SameSite Attribute None

    Source raised by a passive scanner (Cookie without SameSite Attribute)

    WASC ID 13

    WASC ID 15

  11. Server Leaks Version Information via "Server" HTTP Response Header Field
